  Locus:
    Page: 367
    Verse: 5
Tags:
  - Possessions
---
Our most valuable possessions are those which can be shared without
lessening -- those which, when shared, multiply. Our least valuable
possessions, on the other hand, are those which, when divided, are
diminished.
